# Trivy allowlist for ops/llm-guard-sidecar/Dockerfile.
#
# Each entry MUST include:
#   - CVE id
#   - which package/path it surfaces in
#   - why we accept the risk (runtime impact analysis)
#
# Most entries here are build-time-only dependencies never executed at
# request-time. The one documented exception (CVE-2026-4372) is a RUNTIME
# dependency whose only attack vector (untrusted model loading) is unreachable
# in this sidecar — see its entry below for the explicit accepted-risk analysis.

# CVE-2026-24049 — wheel: Privilege Escalation via malicious wheel file.
# Surfaces inside pip/_vendor/wheel-*/METADATA and setuptools/_vendor/wheel-*/METADATA.
# Runtime impact: ZERO. The sidecar only serves HTTP scan requests (FastAPI
# + BERT inference); it never invokes pip to install packages at runtime.
# Exploitable only if an attacker controls a .whl being pip-installed — which
# happens only at image build time from pypi (our CI-controlled source).
CVE-2026-24049

# CVE-2026-23949 — jaraco.context: Path traversal via malicious tar archives.
# Surfaces inside pip/_vendor/jaraco.context-*/METADATA (transitive dep of
# setuptools). Runtime impact: ZERO. The sidecar never parses tar archives —
# uvicorn + llm-guard + FastAPI operate entirely on JSON request bodies.
CVE-2026-23949

# CVE-2026-4372 — transformers 4.51.3: RCE via untrusted model deserialization
# (fixed upstream in transformers 5.3.0). RUNTIME dependency (BERT inference),
# NOT build-time — so the generic doctrine above does not apply; this is an
# explicit accepted-risk, signed off 2026-07-12.
# Why unreachable here: the RCE requires loading an attacker-controlled model.
# This sidecar loads ONLY its own pinned protectai models (PromptInjection,
# Anonymize, Toxicity, NoRefusal, Bias, Sensitive, Relevance), baked at image
# build time from the CI-controlled source; no model path, repo id, or weights
# are ever taken from a request. The sidecar is network-isolated (internal-only,
# reached solely by the backend over the compose network) and its HTTP surface
# accepts JSON scan payloads only — never model files or model identifiers.
# Cannot fix by bumping: llm-guard 0.3.16 (latest) hard-pins transformers==4.51.3
# (Requires-Dist), and no llm-guard release yet supports transformers >=5.3.0.
# Re-evaluate + drop this entry when llm-guard ships transformers-5 support.
CVE-2026-4372
